{
  "stem": "17426.4",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "And hard to believe was also the fact as I later found out, that my mother and my sister were asphyxiated in a truck, in one of those closed-body trucks like a UPS truck, in which the carbon monoxide was diverted inside the car.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "So when they arrived in Chelmno, they were dead.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "And a group of Jews that were kept in Chelmno for the purpose of cremating them, cremated them, spread their ashes through the woods of Chelmno.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "I have been to Chelmno in 1985, before I wrote my book.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "Before I wrote my memoir.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And I saw the inscription which proclaimed that 400,000 Jews were turned into ashes there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And I also saw the monument that is erected on which it says, in Polish, [POLISH], which means we remember.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And on the other side of the monument, the words that they found written in blood inside at liberation-- that we are here.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "We're being shot.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "We're being gassed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "We're being turned into ashes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And we are only here to destroy the bodies.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "We too will be dead at the end of the war.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "I must say that this moved me more than Auschwitz, moved me more than anything that I have seen on my 1985 trip to Poland, Romania, Hungary, Czechoslovakia, and France.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "I think this was so [? desolate ?] and so godforsaken and so morbid that it was hard to take.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "I turned away with my memories that still remain, to this day, inseparable.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "Because they hurt, even 50 years after.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
